<p class="BubbleTitleSub">The Caged Lion: A Short Analysis of British Military Expeditionary Capability in the Days of Austerity</p>
<p>By ARCIC International Army Programs Directorate (IAPD), March 28, 2014</p>
<p>The British military is easily among the most professional and capable military forces in the world. It has a long history of punching above its weight and winning when victory seemed impossible. In the current political environment Her Majesty's Government seeks to reduce military expenditure while maintaining strategic and ideological commitments. This reduction in military spending has greatly reduced the British military's ability to unilaterally project expeditionary power across the globe. In effect the British lion is caged upon its island.</p>
